Example 1. In $\triangle A B C$, $\angle C=3 \angle A$, $a=27, c=48$. What is $b=$ ?
(A) 33 ;
(B) 35;
(C) 37 ;
(D) 39 ;
(E) The value of $b$ is not unique.

[36th American High School Mathematics Examination (February 26, 1985, Beijing), Question 28]

Your publication provided a trigonometric solution to this problem in the 3rd issue of 1985. Now, we will use the aforementioned necessary and sufficient condition to solve it.

